qas.question: Where was Hyderabad ranked in 2012 as a producer of GDP in Talangana?

What was the GDP of Hyderabad in US dollars in 2011-2012?
How many people were employed by the Andhra Pradesh government in 2006?

context: Hyderabad is <a0_0>the largest<a0_0/> contributor to the gross domestic product (GDP), tax and other revenues, of Telangana, and the <a1_0>sixth largest<a1_0/> deposit centre and fourth largest credit centre nationwide, as ranked by the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) in June 2012. Its US<a2_0>$74 billion<a2_0/> GDP made it the fifth-largest contributor city to India's overall GDP in 2011–12. Its per capita annual income in 2011 was ₹44300 (US$660). As of 2006[update], the largest employers in the city were the governments of Andhra Pradesh (<a3_0>113,098<a3_0/> employees) and India (85,155). According to a 2005 survey, 77% of males and <a4_0>19%<a4_0/> of females in the city were employed. The service industry remains dominant in the city, and 90% of the employed workforce is engaged in this sector.
